  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bringing Solar Power and Renewable Energy to Remote Communities in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Govt and NGOs have been implementing PSFs to treat surface water. Water from surface water is pumped through sand filters that work on the principal of &quot;slow sand filter&quot; on a constant flow, which creates biological film on sand layers, formed through a constant flow that removes harmful bacteria. Without constant flow of water bacteria remains and causes water borne disease. Using 6 -solar powered pond sand filters we will provide safe clean drinking water to 8,000 people. Project is funded by GDS Services International and will be implemented by Progoti in Satkhira and Banchte Shekha in Jessore district.</narrative>
  </description>
